00:45:03.552 --> 00:45:06.010
about this is what the Chinese
people know and this is what

00:45:06.010 --> 00:45:06.460
they don't.

00:45:06.460 --> 00:45:07.830
AUDIENCE: But specifically
in the media, has it been--

00:45:07.830 --> 00:45:08.170
RORY TRUEX: Yeah.

00:45:08.170 --> 00:45:09.730
So I would say
that the depiction

00:45:09.730 --> 00:45:11.920
of this in the
Chinese media has been

00:45:11.920 --> 00:45:14.410
that this wasn't a big deal.

00:45:14.410 --> 00:45:17.170
And a lot of the
outcry that occurred

00:45:17.170 --> 00:45:18.880
was among people
like me, foreigners

00:45:18.880 --> 00:45:21.140
who study China or
write about China.

00:45:21.140 --> 00:45:23.560
And the reason it was
pinned as not a big deal

00:45:23.560 --> 00:45:26.380
is because actually, the
position of President

00:45:26.380 --> 00:45:27.849
in the People's
Republic of China,

00:45:27.849 --> 00:45:29.890
if you actually look at
the Chinese constitution,

00:45:29.890 --> 00:45:31.870
it's basically a
ceremonial position.

00:45:31.870 --> 00:45:36.290
So that office is not, in and
of itself, that important.

00:45:36.290 --> 00:45:38.230
It's important because
the person who inhabits

00:45:38.230 --> 00:45:40.790
it is the head of the party.

00:45:40.790 --> 00:45:43.374
So that's one reason why it
was deemed not that important.

00:45:43.374 --> 00:45:45.040
The second reason is
that there actually

00:45:45.040 --> 00:45:47.620
are no term limits on the
position of General Secretary

00:45:47.620 --> 00:45:49.090
of the Communist Party.

00:45:49.090 --> 00:45:51.070
So that position has
never had any term limits.

00:45:51.070 --> 00:45:52.960
There's been a norm
that that person only

00:45:52.960 --> 00:45:55.630
stays in power for two terms,
but there was never actually

00:45:55.630 --> 00:45:57.440
anything on paper
that prescribed that.

00:45:57.440 --> 00:46:00.340
So the way this was positioned,
and among people in China

00:46:00.340 --> 00:46:03.510
who were describing this, was
that all this reform does,

00:46:03.510 --> 00:46:06.220
all this amendment does is put
the position of the presidency,

00:46:06.220 --> 00:46:08.437
it syncs it up with the
position of the General

00:46:08.437 --> 00:46:11.020
Secretary the Communist Party,
so now nothing has term limits.

00:46:11.020 --> 00:46:12.970
So that's the way
it was phrased.

00:46:12.970 --> 00:46:16.370
But for those of us on
the outside looking in,

00:46:16.370 --> 00:46:19.630
it seems that this is a very
obvious example of an existing

00:46:19.630 --> 00:46:23.200
institution that was designed
to curb excess abuses of power,

00:46:23.200 --> 00:46:26.800
accumulation of
power, being eroded.

00:46:26.800 --> 00:46:29.590
So my sense is that the average
Chinese citizen is probably not

00:46:29.590 --> 00:46:31.810
in uproar about
this, but I think

00:46:31.810 --> 00:46:34.210
it does remain a pretty
significant political event.

00:46:34.210 --> 00:46:39.150
In terms of Confucianism, one
of the elements of Xi Jinping

00:46:39.150 --> 00:46:42.240
has been not just the
nationalism in a foreign policy

00:46:42.240 --> 00:46:44.820
front, but a cultural
nationalism, and the Communist

00:46:44.820 --> 00:46:48.510
Party as being the bearer of
Chinese cultural traditions.

00:46:48.510 --> 00:46:52.410
So Confucianism--
I am no expert,

00:46:52.410 --> 00:46:54.030
but there are elements
of Confucianism

00:46:54.030 --> 00:46:56.490
that are conducive to
authoritarian rule,

00:46:56.490 --> 00:46:58.500
in particular the
emphasis on hierarchy

00:46:58.500 --> 00:47:01.500
and the relationship between
the ruled and the ruler.

00:47:01.500 --> 00:47:04.500
And so we've seen a
resurgence of Confucianism

00:47:04.500 --> 00:47:07.810
and the emphasis on
Confucianism in China,

00:47:07.810 --> 00:47:10.350
especially as an alternative
to foreign ideologies

00:47:10.350 --> 00:47:12.160
like Christianity and so forth.

00:47:12.160 --> 00:47:13.230
So I don't believe--

00:47:13.230 --> 00:47:14.799
I'd have to look back.

00:47:14.799 --> 00:47:16.590
There's a whole book
on Xi Jinping Thought,

00:47:16.590 --> 00:47:20.340
and I couldn't get through
it, to be honest with you.

00:47:20.340 --> 00:47:22.920
But I don't believe it's
mentioned in great detail.

00:47:22.920 --> 00:47:25.050
But culturally and
politically, it

00:47:25.050 --> 00:47:28.410
has been an emphasis to focus
on traditional Chinese culture

00:47:28.410 --> 00:47:29.430
and heritage.

00:47:29.430 --> 00:47:32.730
And the Communist Party and Xi
Jinping are protectors of that.

00:47:32.730 --> 00:47:34.304
Thank you.

00:47:34.304 --> 00:47:36.529
Yes.

