00:49:54.485 --> 00:49:56.110
AUDIENCE: Could you
expand a little bit

00:49:56.110 --> 00:49:58.360
on the world's
largest parliament?

00:49:58.360 --> 00:50:00.250
I know you made a point
about how well it's

00:50:00.250 --> 00:50:02.140
orchestrated by the party.

00:50:02.140 --> 00:50:04.412
But what's it like
in its daily affairs?

00:50:04.412 --> 00:50:06.120
How often does that
orchestration happen?

00:50:06.120 --> 00:50:06.954
How deep does it go?

00:50:06.954 --> 00:50:08.911
RORY TRUEX: Thank you
for asking this question.

00:50:08.911 --> 00:50:10.660
So this was the topic
of my dissertation,

00:50:10.660 --> 00:50:14.620
so this brings me back to a
sad, lonely, depressing time

00:50:14.620 --> 00:50:15.220
in my life.

00:50:15.220 --> 00:50:18.190
[LAUGHTER]

00:50:18.190 --> 00:50:20.260
So I'll just give a brief
answer because I could

00:50:20.260 --> 00:50:21.426
talk about this for a while.

00:50:21.426 --> 00:50:24.280
But the National People's
Congress is China's parliament.

00:50:24.280 --> 00:50:26.560
And it has 3,000 members.

00:50:26.560 --> 00:50:30.040
It meets only once per
year for two weeks.

00:50:30.040 --> 00:50:32.200
So you can imagine,
such an institution

00:50:32.200 --> 00:50:35.782
is not exactly a forum for
great policy discussion.

00:50:35.782 --> 00:50:37.240
And they sit in a
large room called

00:50:37.240 --> 00:50:39.406
the Great Hall of the People
which has 3,000 people.

00:50:39.406 --> 00:50:42.790
So often when you hear about
the National People's Congress,

00:50:42.790 --> 00:50:45.010
you hear the words rubber stamp.

00:50:45.010 --> 00:50:46.470
And there is some truth to that.

00:50:46.470 --> 00:50:48.460
So nothing ever
before the parliament

00:50:48.460 --> 00:50:49.840
in the history of
the institution

00:50:49.840 --> 00:50:53.620
before the full body has
ever been voted down ever.

00:50:53.620 --> 00:50:58.360
So if that's not a rubber
stamp, I don't know what is.

00:50:58.360 --> 00:51:00.340
That said, so one of
the arguments I make--

00:51:00.340 --> 00:51:01.870
I did write a book on this.

00:51:01.870 --> 00:51:04.390
It's one of those books
that I wouldn't wish it

00:51:04.390 --> 00:51:06.676
on anybody to read it,
but if you're interested--

00:51:06.676 --> 00:51:08.800
I have a forum, I might as
well self-promote-- it's

00:51:08.800 --> 00:51:11.002
called "Making Autocracy Work."

00:51:11.002 --> 00:51:13.210
But the argument I try to
make is that actually, this

00:51:13.210 --> 00:51:15.543
is one of those institutions
that the Communist Party is

00:51:15.543 --> 00:51:19.750
trying to use to channel
citizen grievances

00:51:19.750 --> 00:51:21.800
through their institutions.

00:51:21.800 --> 00:51:23.860
So rather than have people
protest on the street

00:51:23.860 --> 00:51:25.480
and potentially
engage in violence,

00:51:25.480 --> 00:51:27.438
they're trying to create
political institutions

00:51:27.438 --> 00:51:29.440
that they control, but
that, nevertheless,

00:51:29.440 --> 00:51:32.304
serve some conduit
of information

00:51:32.304 --> 00:51:33.970
that the government
can then respond to.

00:51:33.970 --> 00:51:36.730
So the People's Congress
system is actually a network

00:51:36.730 --> 00:51:37.870
of these institutions.

00:51:37.870 --> 00:51:42.309
There are five different levels
of government, and all the way

00:51:42.309 --> 00:51:44.600
on down to what's known as
the township level in China.

00:51:44.600 --> 00:51:46.450
And there are
hundreds of thousands

00:51:46.450 --> 00:51:48.660
of legislators in China.

00:51:48.660 --> 00:51:50.381
People's deputies,
they're called.

00:51:50.381 --> 00:51:51.880
And so what I've
argued in this book

00:51:51.880 --> 00:51:53.590
is that these
people, their task is

00:51:53.590 --> 00:51:55.930
to go out, and learn
about the population,

00:51:55.930 --> 00:51:58.300
and try to convey
this information

00:51:58.300 --> 00:51:59.970
to the central government.

00:51:59.970 --> 00:52:01.960
But this shouldn't be
confused with democracy.

00:52:01.960 --> 00:52:04.900
This shouldn't be confused
with full representation.

00:52:04.900 --> 00:52:07.630
These people are handpicked
by the Communist Party,

00:52:07.630 --> 00:52:10.480
and they are not allowed
to cross the boundaries.

00:52:10.480 --> 00:52:12.760
So you'll never hear about
a People's Congress deputy

00:52:12.760 --> 00:52:15.260
saying, oh, maybe we should
talk more about the surveillance

00:52:15.260 --> 00:52:17.890
state, or maybe we should have
elections for the position

00:52:17.890 --> 00:52:18.740
of the presidency.

00:52:18.740 --> 00:52:21.325
So it's a very
constrained system.

00:52:21.325 --> 00:52:23.336
But thank you for that question.

00:52:23.336 --> 00:52:24.460
That's the easy one for me.

